4. The function then creates two arrays, one for the elements less than the pivot and one for the elements greater than the pivot.
5. The function then calls the quicksort function recursively on the lesser and greater arrays.
6. The function then combines the lesser and greater arrays together and returns the result.

The bug in the function is that the code is not handling the case when the pivot is the only element in the array.

